line=44 fonts=F0-13.0,F2-13.0 bbox=56.68,737.12,497.11,750.12 iscore=0.17              :(5)   Case languages.  The argument hierarchy is encoded by abstract case features:
line=45 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,722.16,358.86,735.12 iscore=0.09                      :      a. Abstract case:     [+hr] ‘there is a higher role’
line=46 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=209.68,707.16,355.25,720.12 iscore=0.83                     :                            [+lr] ‘there is a lower role’
line=47 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,692.16,370.14,705.12 iscore=0.00                      :      b. These features are realized by morphological case:
line=48 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=209.68,677.17,297.66,690.13 iscore=0.00                     :                            [+hr] accusative
line=49 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=209.68,662.17,285.4,675.13 iscore=1.00                      :                            [+lr] ergative
