line=56 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,555.36,444.16,568.32 iscore=0.00                      :      An  ergative set must contain nonlocal pronominal affixes (see (6c)).
line=57 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,540.36,538.62,553.32 iscore=0.13                      :      Most  case languages exhibit 3rd person pronouns, and in many of them case is gene-
line=58 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,525.36,232.13,538.32 iscore=0.07                      :      ralized to the direct setting.
line=59 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=56.68,504.36,538.64,517.32 iscore=0.15                      :(6)   Fundamental  asymmetry.  The direct setting is more natural than the inverse setting
line=60 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,489.36,539.06,502.32 iscore=0.13                      :      because local person tends to be an agent. Therefore, the inverse setting is more likely
line=61 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,474.36,249.9,487.32 iscore=0.13                       :      to be marked morphologically.
line=62 fonts=F0-13.0,F1-13.0 bbox=90.64,459.36,538.58,472.4 iscore=0.15               :      Expressed by the harmonic  alignment of two scales (Prince & Smolensky 1993, Stie-
line=63 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,444.36,404.21,457.32 iscore=0.31                      :      bels 2000a/b; see also Aissen 1999a for a different account).
line=64 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,429.37,510.55,442.33 iscore=0.27                      :      a. +hr   > +lr                    The morphological marking  by [+hr] is more
line=65 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=277.72,414.37,417.9,427.33 iscore=0.14                      :                                        effective than that by [+lr].
line=66 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,398.48,403.49,411.49 iscore=0.12                     :         +loc  >  −loc                  Person hierarchy (1 > 3)
line=67 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,383.41,295.01,396.37 iscore=0.12                      :      b. Case in the context of person values
