line=162 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=260.68,306.36,277.24,319.32 iscore=0.00                                                                 :                                    obl
line=163 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=56.68,285.36,538.65,298.32 iscore=0.00                                                                  :(16)  Salience case is simply [+ls], but restricted to the direct setting. It is similar to the
line=164 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,270.36,538.7,283.32 iscore=0.12                                                                   :      active marking insofar as an element of the (more natural) direct setting is marked. In
line=165 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,255.36,356.83,268.32 iscore=0.07                                                                  :      this constellation, the following scales are relevant:
line=166 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,240.36,207.28,253.32 iscore=0.14                                                                  :      a. Scales:  +ls > +hs
line=167 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=158.68,224.48,205.6,237.48 iscore=0.33                                                          :                  +lr > +hr
line=168 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,209.4,225.75,222.36 iscore=0.33                                                                   :      b. Markedness  hierarchy:
line=169 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,194.4,527.94,207.36 iscore=0.08                                                                  :         *(+ls)/+hr »*(+ls)/+lr  Salience case is more marked for a lower than a higher
line=170 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=243.64,179.4,295.73,192.36 iscore=0.09                                                                  :                                 argument.
line=171 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,164.4,140.09,177.36 iscore=0.00                                                                   :      c. Tewa:
line=172 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,149.4,515.82,162.36 iscore=0.09                                                                  :         *(+ls)/+hr » Max(+ls)   Realize salience case except for the lower argument.
line=173 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,128.4,532.7,141.36 iscore=0.21                                                                    :      Consequently, there is some chance that the salience case will develop to an ergative.
line=174 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=56.68,107.4,225.66,120.36 iscore=0.07                                                                   :(17)  Possible reinterpretations:
line=175 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=90.64,91.52,505.72,104.52 iscore=0.08                                                           :      b. inverse voice  →   inactive marking  ⎢  accusative case →  passive voice
line=176 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=90.64,75.56,503.57,88.56 iscore=0.67                                                            :      b. direct voice   →   active marking    ⎢  salience case   →  ergative case

