line=178 fonts=F0-13.0,F2-13.0 bbox=56.68,753.2,536.12,766.2                                                                    :(18)  Gaps  for inverse settings. The salience features are relevant in order to explain gaps.
line=179 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,738.24,538.97,751.2 iscore=0.21                                                               :      a. All Tanoan  languages realize the less salient argument of the inverse setting by
line=180 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,723.24,538.64,736.2 iscore=0.27                                                              :         oblique marking in the syntax (which is, as Klaiman has argued, not a passive); in
line=181 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,708.25,444.66,721.21 iscore=0.20                                                             :         other words, they exhibit a gap in the set of structural arguments.
line=182 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,688.07,519.16,703.57 iscore=0.17                                                      :      b. *(arg_{dir})/(+hs)/+lr » Max(arg_{dir}) Realize all arguments structurally except in
line=183 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=294.64,674.88,516.44,687.84 iscore=0.43                                                             :                                          those instances where the lower salience is
line=184 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=294.64,659.88,496.13,672.84 iscore=0.14                                                             :                                          coupled with the higher argument role.
line=185 fonts=F0-13.0,F2-13.0,F3-13.0 bbox=56.68,638.84,524.08,651.84 iscore=0.00                                              :(19)  Operations  restricted to inverse settings: Agent Focus in Tzotzil (Mayan), which
line=186 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,623.04,365.19,636.0 iscore=0.18                                                               :      only applies in inverse 3→3 settings (Aissen 1999b).
line=187 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,607.92,538.61,620.88 iscore=0.15                                                              :      All Mayan  languages exhibit Agent Focus (AF)  where the Agent (the higher argu-
line=188 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,592.92,484.15,605.88 iscore=0.08                                                              :      ment) is focused and extracted from the transitive VP, yielding the structure
line=189 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0,F0-8.0,F0-8.5,F0-9.0,F4-13.0 bbox=90.64,575.27,482.8,590.76 iscore=0.14                          :      •  NP_{+}_{FOC} [_{CP} [_{VP} V-NOMi NP_{i} _ ] rather than [_{VP} V-NOMi-ERGk NP_{i} NP_{k}]
line=190 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=90.64,562.04,495.79,575.04 iscore=0.29                                              :      •  The AF  morpheme  [+FOC]/+lr assigns [+FOC] to the higher argument role.
line=191 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=90.64,546.2,523.63,559.2 iscore=0.25                                                :      •  *(+lr)/+FOC                    Do not realize ergative on a focused argument.
line=192 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0,F0-8.5,F4-13.0 bbox=90.64,528.47,532.12,543.96 iscore=0.33                                       :      •  *(arg_{+}_{FOC})/VP » Max(arg_{+}_{FOC}) A focused argument must be extracted from VP.
line=193 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,501.13,538.6,514.09 iscore=0.33                                                               :      a. Some  Mayan  languages have obligatory AF for every higher argument (Jakaltek,
line=194 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,486.13,231.17,499.09 iscore=0.18                                                             :         Ixil, K’iche’, Tz’utujil).
line=195 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,471.13,538.62,484.09 iscore=0.08                                                              :      b. Tzotzil, however, requires Agent Focus only when  the less salient argument is
line=196 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,456.13,507.4,469.09 iscore=0.17                                                              :         associated with the higher argument role, and both arguments are 3rd person.
line=197 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,438.56,418.36,453.97 iscore=0.25                                                     :         Here, the AF morpheme  is restricted to [+FOC]/(+hs_{−loc})/+lr
line=198 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,426.13,538.66,439.09 iscore=0.14                                                              :      c. There are also Mayan  languages in which  AF  has an antipassive effect (Mam,
line=199 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,411.11,371.68,424.09 iscore=0.08                                                     :         Q’eqchi), so *(+lr)/+FOC is automatically satisfied.
line=200 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,396.12,483.8,409.08 iscore=0.08                                                               :      d. AF  in Jakaltek (type a)      Tzotzil (type b)        Mam   (type c)
line=201 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=144.88,380.24,523.96,393.25 iscore=0.44                                             :                λy   λx  VERB(x,y)     λy    λx  VERB(x,y)     ∃y    λx  VERB(x,y)
line=202 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=141.64,365.28,462.89,378.24 iscore=0.56                                                             :               +hr   +lr               +hr   +lr               +hr   +lr
