line=204 fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0 bbox=311.68,335.27,339.36,348.24 iscore=0.50                                                     :                                             +FOC
line=205 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,320.28,538.66,333.24 iscore=0.00                                                              :      f. There is some evidence  that AF originally was an inverse morpheme (there are
line=206 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,305.28,538.62,318.24 iscore=0.31                                                             :         two such morphemes,  dependent on whether local person is involved or not), and
line=207 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,290.28,500.5,303.24 iscore=0.46                                                              :         was then reinterpreted as [+foc]; only Tzotzil preserved the inverse context.
line=208 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,274.45,528.28,287.41 iscore=0.08                                                              :      g. Navajo (Athabaskan) is another language with inverse marking only in 3→3 sett.
