line=213 tag=G span_id=105-11 lang_name=Tzotzil lang_code=tzc fonts=F0-10.6,F0-13.0 iscore=0.33 bbox=107.68,193.31,309.96,206.28:         the woman   CP-help-AF  the Pedro-FC
line=214 fonts=F0-14.0 bbox=56.68,171.36,389.16,185.4 iscore=0.00                                                               :There are two interesting corollaries for inverse languages:
line=215 fonts=F0-13.0,F2-14.0 bbox=56.68,155.09,538.65,169.13 iscore=0.38                                                      :1.    The obvious need for distinguishing salience in every transitive setting (which seems
line=216 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,140.16,259.38,153.12 iscore=0.17                                                              :      to have become a disadvantage).
line=217 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=90.64,124.33,538.66,137.29 iscore=0.07                                                              :      a. 1→2   and 2→1  cannot  be expressed alike, one person must be the higher one.
line=218 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,109.2,531.0,122.16 iscore=0.21                                                               :         Algonquian languages: a further pair of direct/inverse voice markers (with 2 > 1).
line=219 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,94.2,538.6,107.16 iscore=0.38                                                                :         Many  American  Indian languages: Portmanteau  forms for at least one of these
line=220 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=107.68,78.32,538.63,91.33 iscore=0.08                                                       :         settings. ⇒ Many  idiosyncratic asymmetries (including so-called morphological
line=221 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=107.68,63.24,530.08,76.2 iscore=0.07                                                                :         taboos) seem to have survived even in languages that do not be inverse any more.

