doc_id=105 page=8 block_id=8-2 bbox=56.68,606.6,538.66,772.21 label=bt 308 318
line=308 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=56.68,759.25,363.53,772.21                    :Is there a unidirectional way in the evolution of languages?
line=309 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=74.68,743.36,538.6,756.36 iscore=0.33 :   •  Inverse marking  can only be realized by morphology. Inverse-marking systems have
line=310 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,728.4,538.63,741.36 iscore=0.25         :      disadvantages in the syntax, but they offer several alternative ways for distinguishing
line=311 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,713.4,538.5,726.36 iscore=0.17          :      arguments  also by  case. Many   languages with  rich morphology  show  relics of
line=312 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,698.4,538.66,711.36 iscore=0.33         :      inverse-marking  when  they realize certain features/arguments only in a direct or
line=313 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,683.4,239.93,696.36 iscore=0.09         :      inverse setting, respectively.
line=314 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=74.68,667.52,538.61,680.52 iscore=0.08:   •  Case  marking can be realized by morphology or syntax. Case-marking systems have
line=315 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,652.44,514.03,665.4 iscore=0.21         :      advantages in the syntax, but do not offer any ways to introduce inverse marking.
line=316 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=74.68,636.56,538.66,649.56 iscore=0.29:   •  There  may  be some  historical exchange between  the active and the inverse type,
line=317 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,621.6,538.62,634.56 iscore=0.15         :      possibly in both directions. However, active-type languages have disadvantages in
line=318 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,606.6,534.93,619.56 iscore=0.31         :      the syntax, too. It is unlikely that a case system will develop to an active-type system.

doc_id=105 page=8 block_id=8-3 bbox=56.68,497.88,538.66,589.49 label=bbt 319 324
line=319 fonts=F2-14.0 bbox=56.68,575.45,123.24,589.49                    :Hypothesis
line=320 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=74.68,559.64,264.39,572.64 iscore=0.00:   •  Morphology  is older than syntax.
line=321 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=74.68,543.8,403.51,556.8 iscore=0.25  :   •  Inverse systems play a major role in the transition to syntax.
line=322 fonts=F0-13.0,F4-13.0 bbox=74.68,527.84,538.59,540.84 iscore=0.27:   •  There is no need for morphology. Once syntax was created, morphology (of the kind
line=323 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,512.88,538.66,525.84 iscore=0.21        :      one  finds in the inverse-type and active-type languages) wasn’t needed anymore.
line=324 fonts=F0-13.0 bbox=92.68,497.88,526.4,510.84 iscore=0.17         :      (Though, it still exists in many of the now endangered rich-morphology languages.)

